<paragraph blockId="1.[151,868,1689,1715]" box="[151,868,1689,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,868,1689,1715]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,868,1689,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
Key to species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[491,716,1689,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[491,641,1689,1715]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Stichopogon</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
from Egypt
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="144" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1759,2018]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
1. Greyish-yellow species; antenna contrasting in colour with scape and pedicel yellow to reddish-yellow, postpedicel and style black (
<figureCitation box="[290,365,1788,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,197,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3 A, B. Stichopogon albellus Loew (♀) habitus, body length = 5.8 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376055/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
)........................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[1271,1436,1788,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albellus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1271,1436,1788,1810]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1271,1284,1788,1810]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1296,1373,1788,1810]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">albellus</emphasis>
Loew
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1759,2018]" box="[151,1436,1817,1839]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1817,1839]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">- Greyish-brown or blackish species; antenna uniformly reddish-yellow, brownish or blackish in colour..................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1759,2018]" box="[151,1429,1847,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<keyLead box="[151,1429,1847,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
2. Abdomen with unicolourous olive-grey tomentum, without bands (
<figureCitation box="[867,937,1847,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1991,2013]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,1061,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1435,1059,1969]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 11 Stichopogon marinus Efflatoun, habitus; A, B. (♀) body length = 5.5 mm; C, D (♂) body length = 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376063/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); supraalar bristles absent.. 
<taxonomicName authority="Efflatoun" authorityName="Efflatoun" box="[1219,1429,1847,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marinus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1219,1429,1847,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1219,1327,1847,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">S. marinus</emphasis>
Efflatoun
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1759,2018]" box="[151,1435,1876,1898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1876,1898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">- Abdomen banded; supraalar bristles present............................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1759,2018]" box="[151,1435,1905,1927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1905,1927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">3. Mystax golden-yellow to golden-brown; antenna yellow to reddish-brown........................................ 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1759,2018]" box="[151,1435,1935,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1935,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">- Mystax white; antenna black........................................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="144" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1759,2018]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
4. Brownish-grey species; antenna yellow with blackish style; legs entirely yellow except 5th tarsal segment brown as claws................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann" authorityName="Wiedemann" box="[1159,1436,1996,2018]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inconstans">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1159,1436,1996,2018]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1159,1290,1996,2018]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">S. inconstans</emphasis>
(Wiedemann)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" box="[151,1435,151,173]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,151,173]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">- Greyish-black species; antenna reddish-yellow to reddish-brown; all femora, apical part of tibiae and apical tarsi black.....5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
5. Setae on first abdominal tergite thin and weak; dististylus of male narrow and distinctly curved; 8th sternite of female with long tufts of hairs touching in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[581,644,212,234]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="17.[151,250,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[252,1321,200,962]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[250,1336,193,969]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 14 A, B. Wings. of Stichopogon deserti, S. elegantulus; C, D Last abdominal segments in female Stichopogon chrysostoma, S. scaliger Loew respectivily." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376066/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Fig.14</figureCitation>
C)............................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Schiner" authorityName="Schiner" box="[1202,1435,212,234]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysostoma">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1202,1435,212,234]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1202,1351,212,234]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. chrysostoma</emphasis>
Schiner
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
- Setae on first abdominal tergite thicker; dististylus of male wider and less curved; tufts of hairs on 8th sternite of female shorter and scattered in middle (
<figureCitation box="[461,529,273,295]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="17.[151,250,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[252,1321,200,962]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[250,1336,193,969]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 14 A, B. Wings. of Stichopogon deserti, S. elegantulus; C, D Last abdominal segments in female Stichopogon chrysostoma, S. scaliger Loew respectivily." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376066/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
D)........................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[1271,1436,273,295]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scaliger">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1271,1436,273,295]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1271,1373,273,295]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. scaliger</emphasis>
Loew
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
6. Mystax consist of few bristles, crowded together at most on the middle third of the face and laterally with fine long white hairs; r4 cell of the wing long, the two veins R4, R5 almost parallel................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart" authorityName="Macquart" box="[1233,1435,332,354]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1233,1435,332,354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1233,1311,332,354]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. pusio</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">- Mystax normal occupying at least the middle two-thirds of the lower part of the face; r4 cell of the wing short or long, veins R4, R5 never parallel......................................................................................7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
7. Abdomen black with tergites 1, 4, 5, 8 covered with white tomentum thus forming white transverse bands (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1300,427,449]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1765,1787]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,987,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,983,1744]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5 Stichopogon beckeri Bezzi, habitus; A, B (♀) body length = 7.1 mm &amp; C, D (♂) body length = 6 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376057/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); legs entirely black, at most tibiae with greyish tomentum.................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezzi" authorityName="Bezzi" box="[1278,1436,456,478]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1278,1436,456,478]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1278,1374,456,478]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. beckeri</emphasis>
Bezzi
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">- Abdomen not as above, covered with silvery-white or greyish tomentum except for a large brown spot on 2nd to 5th tergites; legs not entirely black, at least basal half of tibiae and metatarsi reddish-yellow to reddish-brown.......................... 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
8. Cell m3 widely open (
<figureCitation box="[433,520,549,571]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="17.[151,250,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[252,1321,200,962]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[250,1336,193,969]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 14 A, B. Wings. of Stichopogon deserti, S. elegantulus; C, D Last abdominal segments in female Stichopogon chrysostoma, S. scaliger Loew respectivily." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376066/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
); pulvilli nearly as long as claws; 1st abdominal segment with dense hairs.............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann" authorityName="Wiedemann" box="[1150,1436,581,603]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Dasypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1150,1436,581,603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1150,1291,581,603]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. elegantulus</emphasis>
(Wiedemann)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
- Cell m3 narrowly open (
<figureCitation box="[454,543,612,634]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="17.[151,250,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[252,1321,200,962]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[250,1336,193,969]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 14 A, B. Wings. of Stichopogon deserti, S. elegantulus; C, D Last abdominal segments in female Stichopogon chrysostoma, S. scaliger Loew respectivily." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376066/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
), pulvilli 0.5 × as long as claws; 1st abdominal segment with scattered hairs................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Theodor" authorityName="Theodor" box="[1251,1436,644,666]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserti">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1251,1436,644,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1251,1341,644,666]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. deserti</emphasis>
Theodor
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
